BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 506.40 Tm (There are two main styles for building web services, and you should know both names. SOAP is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 491.20 Tm (the older, heavier one, based on XML. REST is the lighter, more flexible style that dominates) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 476.00 Tm (today - and the one we will use. Let me be fair though - SOAP is not the villain; it is just from an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 460.80 Tm (earlier era.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 440.60 Tm (Read across the table with me. SOAP is a strict protocol with rigid rules; REST is a flexible style) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 425.40 Tm (with guidelines. SOAP only speaks XML, which is bulky; REST usually uses JSON, which is light.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 410.20 Tm (SOAP is heavier and slower; REST is lightweight and fast. SOAP needs a formal contract file;) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 395.00 Tm (REST does not.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 374.80 Tm (Here is where each lives today, so you have context. REST is everywhere now - web, mobile,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 359.60 Tm (microservices. SOAP still survives in older banking, payments, and big government systems,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 344.40 Tm (where its strict rules and built-in security were valued. So you will meet REST constantly, and you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 329.20 Tm (will bump into SOAP occasionally in older codebases. Today, and for most of your career, REST is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 314.00 Tm (the answer.) Tj ET
