BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 176.80 Tm (REST is defined by a set of rules, or constraints. Now, I am not going to make you memorise all) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 161.60 Tm (six today - relax. But knowing they exist helps you understand why REST apps are built the way) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 146.40 Tm (they are. Let me touch each one lightly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 126.20 Tm (Stateless - every request carries everything the server needs; the server remembers nothing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 111.00 Tm (between requests. Client-server - the front end and the data side are separate and can change) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 95.80 Tm (independently. Uniform interface - a consistent, predictable way to reach things. Cacheable -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 80.60 Tm (responses can say whether they are safe to store and reuse. Layered system - there can be) Tj ET
