BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 530.50 Tm (Now the practical heart of REST. REST uses the standard HTTP methods as verbs - little action) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 515.30 Tm (words - and beautifully, the four main ones line up exactly with the four things you do with data,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 500.10 Tm (which we call CRUD: Create, Read, Update, Delete.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 479.90 Tm (Let me map them. GET means read existing data - GET slash students lists all students. POST) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 464.70 Tm (means create new data - POST slash students adds a student. PUT means update existing data -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 449.50 Tm (PUT slash students slash one updates student one. And DELETE means remove - DELETE slash) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 434.30 Tm (students slash one.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 414.10 Tm (Here is the mental model I want you to carry. Picture a student record. You GET it to look at it. You) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 398.90 Tm (POST a new one when a student joins. You PUT to fix their email. And you DELETE when they) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 383.70 Tm (leave. Notice the noun stays the same the whole time - slash students - and only the verb changes) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 368.50 Tm (for each action. That is the entire mental model of a REST API. Same noun, different verbs.) Tj ET
