BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 260.80 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 244.80 Tm (Every response from a web service comes with a little number called a status code, which tells the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 229.60 Tm (caller what happened. There are dozens, but you only need five today, and they come in friendly) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 214.40 Tm (groups. Two-hundreds mean success. Four-hundreds mean the caller made a mistake.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 199.20 Tm (Five-hundreds mean the server broke.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 179.00 Tm (Let me give you the five. 200 OK - it worked; Spring sends this automatically for a successful read.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 163.80 Tm (201 Created - used after you successfully create something with POST; you will set this one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 148.60 Tm (yourself. 400 Bad Request - the caller sent something malformed, like broken JSON. 404 Not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 133.40 Tm (Found - the thing you asked for does not exist, like a student ID that is not there. And 500 Server) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 118.20 Tm (Error - your own code crashed with an unhandled error; we will learn to handle those gracefully in) Tj ET
