BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 646.30 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 630.30 Tm (Let's talk about designing good web addresses - what we call URIs. There is one golden rule in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 615.10 Tm (REST, and if you remember it, your APIs will look professional: URIs are nouns, and HTTP) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 599.90 Tm (methods are verbs. In plain words - do not put the action in the address. Let the method say what) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 584.70 Tm (you are doing; the address just names the thing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 564.50 Tm (Look at the good examples on the left. slash students for the whole collection. slash students slash) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 549.30 Tm (one for a specific student. And a query like question-mark name equals John for filtering. Clean,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 534.10 Tm (simple nouns.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 513.90 Tm (Now the bad examples on the right - slash getStudent, slash deleteStudentById, slash student) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 498.70 Tm (slash fetch. See the problem? The verb is jammed into the address, which is clumsy and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 483.50 Tm (redundant, because the HTTP method already says GET or DELETE. It is like naming a file) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 468.30 Tm ('open-this-file dot text' - the action does not belong in the name.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 448.10 Tm (So the pattern to internalise: plural nouns for collections, a path piece to pick one item, and query) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 432.90 Tm (parameters for optional filtering. The verb is never in the URL.) Tj ET
