BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 344.60 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 328.60 Tm (Here is a neat little tidiness trick. When you put at-RequestMapping slash students at the top of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 313.40 Tm (the class - on the class itself - it sets a common prefix for every method inside. So each method's) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 298.20 Tm (address is then just the part after slash students. You write slash students once, not on every) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 283.00 Tm (method.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 262.80 Tm (Look at the before-and-after. On the left, without it, every method repeats slash students - slash) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 247.60 Tm (students, slash students slash all, slash students slash id - over and over. Repetitive, and if you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 232.40 Tm (ever rename it, you have to change it everywhere. On the right, with the class-level mapping, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 217.20 Tm (methods just say the suffix - nothing, or slash all, or slash id. Much cleaner.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 197.00 Tm (How does Spring build the full address? It simply glues the class prefix and the method part) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 181.80 Tm (together. Class slash students, plus method slash id, equals slash students slash id. And the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 166.60 Tm (lovely bonus - change that prefix in one place and every endpoint moves with it automatically. It is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 151.40 Tm (like writing the street name once at the top of a list of house numbers, instead of on every line.) Tj ET
