0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 683.50 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 672.50 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (Now, a practical question - how do you actually test these endpoints? For a GET, you can just type) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.30 Tm (the address in a browser. But you cannot easily test a POST or a PUT from a browser address) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 626.10 Tm (bar, because browsers only do GET. So we use proper API testing tools, and you will meet two) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 610.90 Tm (today.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (The first is Postman. It is a dedicated app for calling APIs, and it gives you full control - you pick) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (the method, set the headers, and paste in a JSON body. This is the industry-standard tool that real) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 560.30 Tm (teams use every day. It is your best friend for testing POST, PUT, and DELETE.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 540.10 Tm (The second is Swagger UI. This one is lovely because it builds itself automatically from your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 524.90 Tm (annotations - zero setup. You add one dependency, and Spring generates a live, interactive web) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 509.70 Tm (page that lists every endpoint with a 'Try it out' button. Look at the mock on screen - that list of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 494.50 Tm (endpoints is generated from your controller; you write no documentation. Great for quick checks) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 479.30 Tm (and for sharing your API with teammates.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 464.10 3.00 214.40 re f
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 0.100 0.100 0.120 rg 1 0 0 1 58.00 445.10 Tm (Slide 16 - ResponseEntity) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 428.10 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 412.10 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 396.10 Tm (Two code panels: a raw return that is always 200, versus ResponseEntity that lets you choose the status.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 382.60 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 371.60 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 355.60 Tm (Let's talk about taking full control of your response. By default, when you return a Student object,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 340.40 Tm (Spring sends it back with status 200 OK. That is fine most of the time. But sometimes you need to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 325.20 Tm (control the whole response - the status code, the headers, everything. That is what) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 310.00 Tm (ResponseEntity gives you - it is a wrapper around the entire response.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 289.80 Tm (Look at the panels. On the left, a plain return - the status is always 200, even when the student) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 274.60 Tm (was not found, which is not quite honest. On the right, using ResponseEntity, you can choose:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 259.40 Tm (return ResponseEntity dot ok with the student for a 200 when it exists, or ResponseEntity dot) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 244.20 Tm (notFound for a clean 404 when it does not.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 224.00 Tm (So when do you reach for it? Whenever the outcome can vary - a 201 Created after a POST, a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 208.80 Tm (404 when something is missing, or when you need to attach special headers. Think of a plain) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 193.60 Tm (return as always mailing a standard envelope, and ResponseEntity as choosing the envelope, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 178.40 Tm (stamp, and the priority yourself. It is the professional way to build precise responses.) Tj ET
