BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (So far, your app has been the provider - it answers requests. But here is a twist: sometimes your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.30 Tm (app needs to be the consumer too. Sometimes your Spring app needs to call another web service) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 626.10 Tm (from inside its own code. For that, Spring has a classic tool called RestTemplate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 605.90 Tm (Look at the snippet. The method getForObject sends a GET request to another service and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (automatically converts the JSON it gets back straight into a Java object. So your app can fetch) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (data from somewhere else and use it. It is synchronous, meaning your code waits for the answer) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 560.30 Tm (before moving on. And there are matching methods for the other verbs too.) Tj ET
